%TUTORIAL ------------------  GDDM/ISPF INTERFACE  -------------------- TUTORIAL
%NEXT SELECTION ===>_ZCMD                                %
+
%                     -----------------------------------
%                     |    Interactive Chart Utility    |
                      -----------------------------------
+
+  The%Interactive Chart Utility+(ICU) is a part of the%Presentation Graphics%
%  Feature+(PGF), which is an optional feature of the Graphical Data Display
   Manager (GDDM) program product.  The Interactive Chart Utility is a program
   which allows a user to quickly and easily produce business charts in a
   readily understood fashion.  The ICU can also be used to generate surface
   charts, histograms, bar charts, pie charts, and Venn diagrams.  A detailed
   discussion of the ICU can be found in the following IBM publication:

     % "Graphical Data Display Manager - Presentation Graphics Feature,
              Interactive Chart Utility User's Guide" - SC33-0111+

   The above manual includes a number of tutorial sessions that show you how
   to use the ICU.  You will find that the best way to learn about the ICU
   is to use it.  In addition tutorial panels are incorporated within the ICU
   and can be displayed by depressing the HELP (PF1/PF13) program function
   key.

)PROC
   &ZUP = ADM#PT0
)END
